  </exercise>

  <lemma xml:id="lecture-notes-lem-how-to-subtract-complex-numbers">
    <title>How to Subtract Complex Numbers</title>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Let <m>a+bi</m> and <m>c+di</m> be any two complex numbers.
        Then
        <me>(a+bi)-(c+di)=(a-c)+(b-d)i</me>.
      </p>
      <p>
        In other words, distribute the negative and add like terms.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </lemma>

